race.comment: The speedy BAZABALL REWARDED (4) didn't run out 1200m here in stronger, but won easily her three prior over 1000m at the track. Jumped a short-priced favourite again and has been kept on the fresh side. Hits this at peak and the promising mare rates to bounce back. BLETHYN (5) resumed in good order with a narrow defeat at Moonee Valley in a 70  and then found an Open 3 at Flemington a stretch too far. Has Stackhouse aboard today and the blinkers go on for the first time. Much better suited and a bold run is on the cards. SEVEN OCEANS (12) didn't finish it off in town but ran a good number winning a Cranbourne Maiden first up prior. Maps well and Williams is a key jockey engagement. Goes in at an each-way price. MIDNIGHT CHARM (1) resumes for the Douglas yard with a 3kg claim. Has had a long spell (no issues) and has three jumpouts under the saddle. He has ability and is likely to race well.
